               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to<persName type="standard"
                               ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736"
                               key="n 80119944 ">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Huntingdon_359-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName ref="supplied">al-Nīlīالنيلي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Talkhīs Sharḥ Jālīnūs li Kitāb al-Fuṣūl maʿa Nukat min sharḥ al-Rāzī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar">تلخيص شرح جالينوس لكتاب الفصول مع نكت من شرح الرازي</title>
                     
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="translated">Abridgment of Galen’s Commentary on the Aphorisms with anecdotes [nukat] from ar-Rāzī’s Commentary</title>
                     <note>This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The introduction begins on f. 1b; the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: 1b; Bk 2: 6a (ending at ii. 40; in f. 10b, Bk 2 ends at ii. 40, and then ii. 23 starts); Bk 3: 10a (starting from iii. 22's comm.); Bk 4: 12b (ending at iv. 35); Bk 5: 15b; Bk 6: 21a; Bk 7: 26b. This is an incomplete copy.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <author key="n 80046950" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/102329635">Savage-Smith</author>,<title>A new catalogue of Arabic manuscripts in the Bodleian Library, University of Oxford</title>
